nodes.name: Daily Minimum Limit
nodes.notes:
(Read DS) >100/week

LinkedIn imposes a weekly limit on connection requests to prevent spam, and by default, you can send around 100 connection requests per week.

Users with a high Social Selling Index (SSI) Score and strong engagement on the platform may extend this limit to up to 200 requests per week. An engaging system could come useful.

fieldValues.fieldDescription:
=The reasearch should aim to get a comprehensive view of the whole company, from the product, all the way to the vision. You want to:

1. Get relevant informations about the product, service, their offer
2. Get general data of their company,
4. Get the company's vision, mission, best testimonials and feedback
3. Get company's sub-links
4. Extract all data inside the company sub-links
5. Get informations about their blog, if there's one
6. Get information about their community, if there's one

options.systemMessage:
You are an expert in evaluating lead potential for our product.
Analyze the company’s and lead’s profile content, assessing their likelihood of interest in our product on a scale from 1 to 10 (where 1 indicates minimal potential, and 10 indicates maximum potential).

Here are the infos of our business and product: [business & product]

Here are the criteria we are looking for:


Evaluation scale:
• 8–10 points: Clear mentions of the criteria, great or excellent match with our business and products, active engagement, and explicit interest.
• 5–7 points: Mention of a few criteria  or indirect indicators of interest in both criteria, good or excellent match with our business and products, indirect interest.
• 1–4 points: No clear mentions, or only weak indirect indicators of interest, low match with our business and products, no or 1 criteria only met.

Your answer must ONLY be a single number from 1 to 10, without any additional text.
